jettySize=auto;exitX=0.5;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="CHDPR" target="PADGHAPG"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="L91" value="HVDC Pole 2" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;strokeColor=#0288D1;strokeWidth=2;fontSize=8;fontColor=#546E7A;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;endArrow=block;endFill=1;jettySize=auto;exitX=0.5;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="CHDPR" target="PADGHAPG"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="legend" value="&lt;b&gt;HOW TO USE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Drag buses / re-route lines to match the SLDC sheet exactly.&lt;br&gt;2. Do NOT rename a bus unless you also want the portal name changed — shapes bind by ID first, label second.&lt;br&gt;3. Delete a wrong circuit; draw a new connector between two buses to add one.&lt;br&gt;4. Parallel circuits: draw a second connector between the same pair.&lt;br&gt;5. Save as .drawio, then upload in Settings &gt; draw.io round-trip.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Magenta = 765 kV&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Red = 400 kV&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Blue = HVDC&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Dashed bus = off-page connector (same station drawn twice)" style="text;html=1;fontSize=12;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#FFF9C4;msetclDecor=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="3400" width="900" height="180" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram></mxfile>